stylometry: The tradeoff/relationship between price and demand is simply an inverse relationship.  As the price of a product or service increases, the demand will decrease and as the price decreases, the demand for that product or service will increase.  If i were to develop a model I would use a product and set it at a reasonable price to see if the demand for the product is reasonable so that I know if I should change the price to maximize the demand for the certain product.
